sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Manager as Kueue Manager<br/>Controller
    participant Queue as Queue Manager<br/>In-Memory Cache
    participant Scheduler as Scheduler Engine
    participant Job as Batch Job / ML Training Job

    %% Flow 1: Job Submission and Admission
    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over User,Job: Flow 1: Job Submission and Admission
        User->>K8sAPI: POST Job (kubectl create)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutate Job Request<br/>mTLS (API Server identity)
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Inject LocalQueue annotation<br/>Set Job suspend=true
        K8sAPI-->>User: Job created (suspended)

        Manager->>K8sAPI: Watch Job resources<br/>ServiceAccount Token
        K8sAPI-->>Manager: Job created event

        Manager->>Manager: Create Workload CR<br/>from Job resource requests
        Manager->>K8sAPI: Create Workload CR<br/>ServiceAccount Token
        K8sAPI-->>Manager: Workload created

        Manager->>Queue: Add Workload to LocalQueue<br/>In-Process
        Queue->>Scheduler: Evaluate admission<br/>In-Process

        alt Resources available
            Scheduler-->>Queue: Admit workload
            Queue-->>Manager: Workload admitted
            Manager->>K8sAPI: Update Workload status=Admitted<br/>Update Job suspend=false
            K8sAPI-->>Job: Job unsuspended (pods created)
            Job-->>K8sAPI: Job running
        else Insufficient resources
            Scheduler-->>Queue: Queue workload
            Queue-->>Manager: Workload pending
            Manager->>K8sAPI: Update Workload status=Pending
            Note over Job: Job remains suspended
        end
    end

    %% Flow 2: Visibility API Query
    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over User,Manager: Flow 2: Visibility API Query
        User->>K8sAPI: GET /apis/visibility.kueue.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/<br/>clusterqueues/{name}/pendingworkloads<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        K8sAPI->>Manager: Proxied API request<br/>8082/TCP HTTPS (internal cert)<br/>API Aggregation
        Manager->>Queue: Query pending workloads<br/>In-Process (cache query)
        Queue-->>Manager: Pending workload summaries<br/>(position, priority, resources)
        Manager-->>K8sAPI: JSON response
        K8sAPI-->>User: Pending workload list
    end

    %% Flow 3: Metrics Collection
    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Manager,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Metrics Collection
        K8sAPI->>Manager: Prometheus scrapes /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (no auth)
        Manager-->>K8sAPI: Metrics (admitted_workloads_total,<br/>pending_workloads, queue_usage)
    end

    %% Flow 4: Multi-Cluster Distribution
    rect rgb(255, 240, 245)
        Note over Manager,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Multi-Cluster Workload Distribution (MultiKueue)
        Note over Manager: Manager cluster evaluates<br/>remote cluster capacity
        Manager->>K8sAPI: Connect to remote cluster API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: KubeConfig credentials
        Manager->>K8sAPI: Create Workload on remote cluster<br/>HTTPS (KubeConfig auth)
        K8sAPI-->>Manager: Workload created on remote

        loop Monitor remote workload
            Manager->>K8sAPI: Watch remote workload status<br/>HTTPS (KubeConfig auth)
            K8sAPI-->>Manager: Status update
        end

        Manager->>Manager: Update local workload status<br/>with remote results
    end
